                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAWAU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at Center for",
                "Experimental Nuclear Physics and Astrophysics",
                " (CENPA) of the University of Washington using 22Na",
                "targets implanted at the radioactive ion beam",
                "facility TRIUMF-ISAC"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three 300 mu-Ci targets of 22Na were fabricated by",
                "rastering the 22Na ion beam over a 5-mm diameter",
                "collimator and into an oxygen-free high-conductivity",
                " (OFHC) copper substrate. 22Na ions were produced by",
                "bombarding thick SiC targets with a 40 mu-A, 500-MeV",
                "proton beam from the TRIUMF cyclotron. A surface",
                "ionization source and a high resolution mass",
                "separator were used to yield a 10-nA, 30-keV beam of",
                "22Na. To prevent sputtering of 22Na by the intense",
                "proton beam during the measurements, two targets",
                "were coated with 20 nm of Cr coating using vacuum",
                "evaporation"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two high purity Ge (HPGe) crystals surrounded",
                "by Pb shielding and scintillators for cosmic-ray",
                "rejection positioned at +- 55 deg."
              ]
            }
